The input `n` is a positive integer.
The length of the input `edges` is equal to `n - 1`.
Each element in the input `edges` is a 2-element array.
Each element in the input `edges` is an array of integers.
Each element in the input `edges` represents an edge between two nodes in the tree.
The input `price` is an array of integers.
The length of the input `price` is equal to `n`.
Each element in the input `price` is a positive integer.
